    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>The moth flaps its wings and emits ultrasonic squeaks that scramble the senses of nearby creatures. Choose one creature within 30 feet of the moth. That creature must attempt a Fortitude save. This uses a trained DC using the moth's Constitution modifier or an expert DC if the moth is specialized.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target treats all creatures as @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Concealed]{Concealed} on its next attack before the start of your next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target treats all creatures as concealed until the start of your next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, and the target is also @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Stunned]{Stunned 1}.</p>"
